# cURL Import and Export Examples

This file demonstrates the cURL import/export functionality of the REST Client.
You can paste cURL commands and convert them to HTTP requests, or copy requests as cURL.

## Basic cURL Examples

### Simple GET Request
# Original cURL:
# curl https://api.github.com/users/octocat

GET https://api.github.com/users/octocat

###

### GET with Headers
# Original cURL:
# curl -H "Accept: application/vnd.github.v3+json" https://api.github.com/repos/zed-industries/zed

GET https://api.github.com/repos/zed-industries/zed
Accept: application/vnd.github.v3+json

###

### POST with JSON Data
# Original cURL:
# curl -X POST https://httpbin.org/post \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"name":"John Doe","email":"john@example.com"}'

POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com"
}

###

### POST with Form Data
# Original cURL:
# curl -X POST https://httpbin.org/post \
#   -d "username=johndoe" \
#   -d "password=secret123"

POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=johndoe&password=secret123

###

## Authentication Examples

### Basic Authentication
# Original cURL:
# curl -u username:password https://httpbin.org/basic-auth/username/password

GET https://httpbin.org/basic-auth/username/password
Authorization: Basic dXNlcm5hbWU6cGFzc3dvcmQ=

###

### Bearer Token Authentication
# Original cURL:
# curl -H "Authorization: Bearer ghp_abc123def456" https://api.github.com/user

GET https://api.github.com/user
Authorization: Bearer ghp_abc123def456

