## Complex Examples

### PUT Request with Multiple Headers
# Original cURL:
# curl -X PUT https://api.example.com/resources/123 \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -H "Accept: application/json" \
#   -H "X-API-Key: abc123xyz" \
#   -H "X-Request-ID: req-001" \
#   -d '{"name":"Updated Resource","status":"active"}'

PUT https://api.example.com/resources/123
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-API-Key: abc123xyz
X-Request-ID: req-001

{
  "name": "Updated Resource",
  "status": "active"
}

###

### DELETE Request with Custom Headers
# Original cURL:
# curl -X DELETE https://api.example.com/resources/456 \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer token123" \
#   -H "X-Confirm-Delete: true"

DELETE https://api.example.com/resources/456
Authorization: Bearer token123
X-Confirm-Delete: true

###

### Request with Special Characters
# Original cURL:
# curl -X POST https://api.example.com/search \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"query":"hello & goodbye","filter":"name='John O'\''Brien'"}'

POST https://api.example.com/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "hello & goodbye",
  "filter": "name='John O'Brien'"
}

